<subSubSection pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1437,1688,1894]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Remarks.—A green and black species with golden pubescence that resembles a miniature of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Distant" authorityYear="1882" box="[1203,1314,1688,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadidae" genus="Malagasia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflata">
<emphasis box="[1203,1314,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">M. inflata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The body size, inflated male abdomen being widest at segment 4, and the curved posteromedial opercular margin can distinguish the species. Body length is about 
<quantity box="[595,676,1760,1787]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="27.0">27 mm</quantity>
, wingspan about 
<quantity box="[871,971,1760,1787]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.65" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="66.5">66.5 mm</quantity>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Boulard, M." box="[985,1158,1760,1787]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="44 - 53" refId="ref66883" refString="Boulard, M. (1980 b) Un dispositif protecteur secondaire inedit pour le systeme acoustique chez quatre cigales malgaches (Hom. Cicadoidea). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France, 85, 44 - 53." type="journal article" year="1980">Boulard 1980b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1437,1688,1894]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
Distribution.—The species is known only from 
<collectingCountry box="[746,881,1796,1822]" name="Madagascar" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Metcalf, Z. P." box="[898,1069,1796,1822]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="1 - 492" refId="ref69874" refString="Metcalf, Z. P. (1963 b) General catalogue of the Homoptera, Fascicle VIII. Cicadoidea. Part 2. Tibicinidae. North Carolina State College Contribution, 1564, i-vi + 1 - 492." type="journal article" year="1963">Metcalf 1963b</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Duffels, J. P. &amp; van der Laan, P. A." box="[1082,1424,1796,1823]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" refId="ref68709" refString="Duffels, J. P. &amp; van der Laan, P. A. (1985) Catalogue of the Cicadoidea (Homoptera, Auchenorhyncha) 1956 - 1980. Series Entomologica 34. Dr. W. Junk Publishers, Dordrect, 414 pp." type="book" year="1985">Duffels &amp; van der Laan 1985</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Boulard, M." box="[151,339,1832,1859]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" pagination="44 - 53" refId="ref66883" refString="Boulard, M. (1980 b) Un dispositif protecteur secondaire inedit pour le systeme acoustique chez quatre cigales malgaches (Hom. Cicadoidea). Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France, 85, 44 - 53." type="journal article" year="1980">Boulard (1980b)</bibRefCitation>
reports the species from Saint Marie Island, East 
<collectingCountry box="[920,1057,1832,1858]" name="Madagascar" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, Antongil Bay, East 
<collectingCountry box="[1295,1432,1832,1858]" name="Madagascar" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, Isaka, Fanjahira Valley, Southeast 
<collectingCountry box="[536,673,1868,1894]" name="Madagascar" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
, and Diégo-Suarez, North 
<collectingCountry box="[972,1109,1868,1894]" name="Madagascar" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
